	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f10034760279890>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>RE: Needs some info</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Oct 19th 3:20 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I have played an enchanter for 15 levels now, but have been grouped with many before(while playing my main)... which ended up making me interested on this class.<br><br>As Glass already pointed out, in the first levels you won't be much of an asset to a group. <br><br>Lacking any Mana recovery spell(breeze/clarity), haste buffs(quickness/alacritiy/clelerity..), and having a weak mesmerize, I spent most of my time soloing.<br><br>I picked Erudite simply because of the high intelligence and decent charisma. The other races can all make good enchanters, but I believe that gnomes may be difficult to begin with, since they have very low charisma, and charisma is very important(some even believe it is more important than intelligence...)<br><br>I leveled in the Everfrost Peaks until I got to level 12(when I got the spell bind affinity). Right now, I am in Eruds Crossing, in the famous willowisp isle... here is where I began having fun! charming willowisps and watch them smack each other silly :)<br><br>Now to the question about being required in groups... as Glass already mentioned, this is one of the easiest classes to get groups... you will only have problems if you have competition around. And even if there is more than 1 enchanter in the zone, I don't think it will be that difficult.Once you get to level 16 and get the spell breeze, it will be hard to not get a /tell asking for you to cast the spell on them or asking for a group :) and it only gets better once you get clarity...<br><br>Enchanters are, btw, the only class capable of buffing mental power... if shamens are the masters of dealing melee crack, chanters are the masters of dealing casters' crack. Oh, yeah, chanters also gain the haste buffs before shamens do(I play a shamaness as well :)<br><br>Now, something you have not asked yet, but may be handy.... about Specialize(level 20). I will probably do alteration, but later may change to conjuration, as my job will be mesmerize in dungeons or anywhere with lots of adds(makes me think of Sarnak fort in LOIO).<br><br>The previous posts covered your question about the spells, so I am done with sharing the little I know. Hope you enjoy this wonderful class.<br><br>Zissi-15 chanter on drinal<br></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
	     <tr><td colspan=2 align=right class=mform id=fs8>1 Replies</td></tr>
	     </form></table><tr><td colspan=2><ul><table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f100545312159101>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=13&mid=100545312159101>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=100545312159101>RE: Needs some info</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=100545312159101#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sat, Nov 10th 11:32 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>While I agree with most of the previous post, I wanted to make one clarification, to your statement of enchanters being "the only class capable of buffing mental power".&nbsp;&nbsp;Actually, Bards have a clarity-like song, (and thus are sometimes known as "mana batteries").  it shows no icon, and needs to be continuous play for the affect (not like heal song for example, where one play of the song gives three "ticks" of benefit - the mana song gives benefit only while being actively played and the mana user has to be in range of the bard, as always...).  <br><br>The truly lovely thing to note about this, is that the spell is stackable with the song!!  This makes a bard/enchanter combo pretty seriously desired, the casters can cast with impunity, and the meleers are buffed, and fighting debuffed mobs...  so everyone is happy.  When I play my bard (mid-30s now), I always look for an enchanter, and vice versa.  <br><br>And I find neither my bard nor my chanter have much trouble finding groups, with our mana-crack, group buffs, enemy debuffs, and charms. fun fun fun.<br><br>Alter<br>Tholuxe Paells</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
